"What's that, sir?"  "The family we've cast for this movie is so pure snow white that I literally went blind for a few minutes during the test screening. text: Okay, I really want to address all this bullshit going down in the comments. First off, this is an unbiased opinion considering one half of my family is Christian and the other half is not. I want to say that all this about God saving this girl, in my honest opinion, is straight out stupid. Okay, I don't care if you believe in God or not, but NATURE saved her from this illness. A tree's limb fell off under the pressure of the 2 little girls' weight, causing one of them to fall. When the girl fell it hit one of the nerves in her brain, saving her from this illness (apparently.) Now to address the comments saying "God saved her because her family was made up of Christians who prayed and asked for God to cure their daughter!!"  No.. Just no. I'm sure many Christians in Paris who died prayed to God to live when they were bombed by terrorists! What makes this girl's life more important to God than those poor Christians? If God loves everyone, why does he choose who lives and who doesn't?

text: About three decades ago when working in a Workers' Compensation and Social Security Disability focused law office, my boss told me that one of his clients took a fall and it fixed her back!  Looking forward to seeing this movie about faith. Our nation needs a lot of that. I'm voting for the Christian man, even if other Christians complain he's "wearing his faith on his sleeve." George Washington wore his faith on his sleeve. Ever since 1962 (when our teachers were leading us in daily prayer; -- in our case The Lord's Prayer), Christians have been increasingly ridiculed as being unscientific. I remember seeing the 1960 move starring Spencer Tracy that made Christians look like dumb, fanatical,  unscientific jerks (INHERIT THE WIND) while failing to disclose that the  bogus evidence of the (1925) Scope trial case was a fraud, a pig's tooth, not the "link" between ape man and hu-man. So glad to see another faith-based movie!!! Thank you!!!!

text: This is a message for anyone that feels like they‚Äôre struggling with sin in their life, or just feel they are struggling in general. Also for skeptics or people who don‚Äôt believe in God at all. Please just give it a read. The least you can do is get more reading in for the day :)   As a Christian, I would never criticize anyone for making decisions that are or lead to sinfulness because I‚Äôve sinned gratefully in my past (I still do today, but to a much lesser degree). I was saved from my sinful life by choosing God‚Äôs will over mine and developing a pure love for others like Jesus showed us. It breaks my heart to see more and more people that feel like they can live without God. I am telling you that if not now, you will eventually find yourself in a place where things are just too hard. At that point you can either turn back to your Creator for strength and direction or fill your life with worldly things just to get through. This is dangerous because those things are usually drugs, alcohol, sex, food, pornography, or rebellion to name a few. These things will ultimately separate us from God even more and destroy our lives while they‚Äôre at it. I know what it‚Äôs like to be practically drowning in sin, but feel totally fine because you have so many worldly things to distract you from the pain. But in the end, you‚Äôll be stuck in a constant search for meaning. The only way to find meaning is through Christ. Believe me, once you ask for forgiveness and let Him into your heart, He will save you from your struggles and you can then live with abundance and fulfillment. The joy God can bring you when you commit yourself to Him is truly unbelievable. I‚Äôm still amazed everyday. I‚Äôd ask you to examine the troubles that plague your life right now. They could be sexual sins, addictions, suicidal thoughts, family problems, people-pleasing, anxiety, promiscuousness, eating disorders, low self-esteem, bitterness, self- harm, depression, crime, jealousy, hopelessness, loneliness- anything. Ask yourself, is my life going to be enjoyable 10 years from now if I don‚Äôt change my ways? Are these ways going to provide for me any of the genuine love God wants to show me?   I‚Äôm not forcing anyone to change or believe in God if they don‚Äôt want to. I just want everyone to be saved like I was saved. I know that some of these worldly things make life easier, heck they may even make it better. But when you have to rely on material things, people included, to feel happy then that‚Äôs not true happiness. True happiness is found in God and God alone. I want all of my brothers and sisters to go to Heaven some day. I also want them to live life abundantly like Jesus promised he can do for us. He surely did for me. You can be saved from an empty life and eternal punishment.   If you want, look up the I AM SECOND Youtube channel. People  share their stories of when they were saved. There are plenty to choose from. I also recommend you read these 3 verses (look them up online if you don‚Äôt have a Bible): Matthew 19: 25-26, Romans 8: 38-39, and John 3:15-17. God Bless all who read this entire thing :) I wish you the best of luck if you chose to seek out the love of God!

text: I just wanted to clarify something so that people can understand at least what the Catholic Church believes based on the argument that God gave her the disease in the first place. I can personally understand why people would say this. Why would a just and all-loving God have a little girl struggle with such a painful disease?  We believe God himself did not give her this disease. Our world is currently in a fallen state, it is not perfect. In the beginning, it was heaven on earth and every creature lived free from pain and disease. God desired most to give human beings "free will." He wanted us to be able to choose him rather than to become his little puppets. However, free will also allowed us to not choose God, which lead to the downfall of humanity, thus also making our world no longer perfect. Because of this, there are unexplained natural disasters and diseases that no one purposefully intended to happen. However, we hold on because there is still hope of a perfect life in heaven.

The I loved about this movie is that Anna's mother was going to do anything for her daughter to feel comfortable and have a normal life.  There are a majority of parents that don't do that.

text: I just want to say that I watch this movie and it touched me and moved me. So many of us who have children never stop to think how lucky we are to have healthy and happy kids. We have a Great God who is loving and merciful and although we may not understand why things happen the way they do, know that God has a plan and his plans are always for good. Through this little girl's illness and then her testimony and miracle healing, this movie was created. So that many others who perhaps don't know Jesus will come to find him and those who do know him will come to realize just how fortunate they are to have him in there life.   P.S. God does reach out to people in many ways. My boyfriend who knew of God had an experience too just like the little girl in the movie and my boyfriend got taken to a mountain where he spoke to Jesus and there was a bright light over head that he believes was God. The conversation was about his self worth as a person. Jesus loves my boyfriend and my boyfriend needed to know that Jesus is real and loves him because sometimes we don't love ourselves and think that God doesn't either but that is not true just a lie from the enemy. Worthiness is not something we have to concern ourselves with because Jesus took care of that on the cross and we don't have to do works to be worthy. All we need to do is realize what Jesus did for us and know how much he loves us and want to have him in our life and heart. John 3:16 For God so Loved the WORLD he gave his only begotten SON, That who so ever believeth in him shall not perish but have ever lasting life. God Bless you all who took the time to read this....

text: Three years ago today almost one month after the birth of Little Miss Chloe, we went through a minor health scare with our little Angel..."Pyloric Stenosis: According to Wikipedia - A condition in which the opening between the stomach and small intestine thickens." In my Google Voice... LoL!I kid about it now, but it was a scary time for us... Weeks of not knowing what was wrong with our New Born & multiple doctors giving misdiagnosis and a determined new mommy, who just knew there was something more.Always listen to your gut... Or in this case your babies gut. üòâBut seriously though; the prayers & support that we received from friends & family during this time was so strong & powerful it really was greatly appreciated in a time when we needed it most...Last year I took the Family to go see "MIRACLES FROM HEAVEN" a true story about a little girl about 8 or 9 that had the same illness as Chloe... The difference being that Chloe's issue was "Hardware" & this little girl's issue was "Software"; or at least that's how I explain it... And just like in this story we were given the run around by doctor after doctor because they are human & don't always have the answers.But this Movie really hit home for us; and I will say that this movie had me BAWLING like never before as it brought back the feelings that we experienced... And it wasn't just the similar illness or the test in faith that got the most out of me... It was near the end of the movie when they reflected back on the PEOPLE, the LOVE and SUPPORT and PRAYERS that came from their Friends and Family and Total Strangers... The "LIVING ANGEL" It showed how Love & Compassion can go a long way.Tonight me & Amber plan on a Pre-Valentines Day Movie Night with this movie & I definitely recommend it to everyone.

text: A little girl from India is blind. Her family is very poor and can't afford treatment. The doctor says that she will be blind forever. The parents are disappointed but what can they do? One day the little girl is walking across the street thinking it is clear when she is hit by a cow. She falls and hits her head. When she wakes up in the hospital she has regained her sight.  The little girl says that when she blacked out she was taken to a giant palace surrounded by elephants, all adorned in gold and pearls. There are four people with multiple arms and hands, they have twelve eyes and two heads. Up the stairs she hears a voice and it is Vishnu. She walks to Vishnu who tells her that she will recover and have perfect sight.  The town claims it a miracle and she is brought to the temple to speak in front of thousands of people. She tells her story. They all praise Vishnu for giving the girl the ability to see.

text: I will be honest.  I am raised in a christian family but I was never a strong believer. Most of the time I would even think God's not real and I doubted him. but one fine day when I stepped over my baby kitten and she was literally lying dead. I prayed so hard. I prayed and prayed for her to be fine. I remember weeping so badly and never ever in my life have I prayed like that. I kept the cat back at her room and I fell asleep..I woke uo the next day and hoped for whatever was to happen. When I entered the room I saw her running towards me all healthy and happy. I was so thrilled and so happy and the first thing I did was thank God for the miracle. because in no way did I think my kitty would survive. she was panting and closing her eyes that I thought I'd lose her. It was that when I realise that when you have true faith in God. he will answer your prayer.

text: Faith, hope, love. Contempary crap. I watched this at its full predictable length. Is it a Christian movie? Let's see. The great message of the Gospel is that Christ Jesus gave His Blood for our sins that we might be saved. Is that the gospel of this movie? Heh...far from it. "Faith, muricals(southern accent), and luv...and hope." When you learn it was backed in production by prosperity Oneness(Jesus-only cultist) T.D. Jakes...for most educated Christians... that was the red light of a false gospel. The girl goes to all doctors and none can heal her. She falls into a tree(similar to the tree from the original 1981 Tobe Hooper film Poltergeist), where she goes into a transcendalist delusion. Mind you, she has a pure Hinduist out-of-body experience with "god." Full of good chakras, kundalini worship mixed with the latest Pearl Jam/Creed impersonating contemprary pop-rock. It's a mix of New Age, Hinduism, Anglican, pseudo-Christian science, and secular feel-good philosphy. The story holds no credibility as this same give faith get miracles(give a seed of faith for $1,000 god will give you your miracles) gospel holds no ground to any true Christian. 1st world, lukewarm, religious white-washing and holds a recycled fable of miracles via faith-healing as all "good" multi-million "christians" like T.D. text: I am going to make some comments here, and before I really say any thing, I am going to say that I am a christian. Jesus is God. And the bible is the measuring rod. Jesus is the Lord. I seen this movie a while ago, and I am thankful to God for testimonies, and miracles, and what ever Jesus is doing amen to that. Thank God for that. And thank God that this girl was ok, and was healed by God.  But seeing this movie, I felt so dissatisfied with the lack of scripture, and the lack of understanding that it brought to people. People have so many questions about the bible, and about God, and because many people don't understand the things that are in the bible, they don't come to God.  The bible says, my people perish for lack of knowledge, and the bible says, you shall know the truth and the truth shall set you free. And the bible says to get knoweldge, and to get understanding.  And the bible says, to always have an answer for the hope that is in you. And maybe the people that made this movie just simply did not know what the bible says about these topics. But it just seems like to me, that there is sooo sooo soooo much more that could have been said.  And some things that were not said rightly at all.  Like where the mother was asked about sins in their family and she got offended. The bible says many will be offended, so you can be sure this is some thing that the devil is going to try to use, offense.  I can see that more and more there is this effort in the spirit, with demons, to silence people. Just to stop them from talking freely. But the bible says, where the spirit of the Lord is there is freedom.  And unless some topic is going to make some one stumble, like some sexual topics may make some men stumble...then any thing I think, other than that should be fair game. There needs to be open discussion in the church, and there needs to be open discussion with people that are not part of the church.  any ways, I want to get to some thing specific. So she was asked about sin in her family, or some thing like that, but then she was offended and walked out.  The right response should have been, show me where I am wrong from the bible.  And you know what those ladies in that show brought up was biblical.  Who was the man that was healed, who was brought through the roof, and Jesus said take up your mat and walk, you sins are forgiven? And then some said, who can forgive sins but God? But Jesus answered them and said, what is easier to say, your sins are forgiven? or take up your mat and walk? So in the mind of God, forgiveness of sins, and healing and one and the same. And that is what these ladies understood, and wanted to get to, I think, to address the sin, that it might be stopped, and forgiven, and that this girl might have been healed.  But the mother took it personal, and was offended, and cut off communication, and this was the wrong move.  People have got to get over the fact that the truth is hard. Truth is not defined by feeling good, or looking pretty. Some times truth is hard. You have bills, and your bank account is empty, well do you say, it seems to bad to be true?  People need to seek the truth, not based on how good or bad it seems on the surface of the story. But they need to look to prove if it is really so or not.  Every christian should be looking to the bible often to see if they measure up. Every christian should be increasing in knowledge and understanding. Every christian should be looking for any thing that could be an excuse for demons to reside in their house, like having some thing stolen. Or having non christian music...I think some people need to pray about that, and also look up John Todd and Rebekka brown.
author: Shane Bob

text: I would really encourage every person that wants to know about healing, and how it works biblical...I speak of supernatural healing, to look up Kenneth E Hagin - The ABC's of bible faith. And I would encourage them to study the bible on the subject, and to look in Hebrews chapter 11.  So many people think that healing should just be all automatic, well if God wants to heal me He will. God is sovereign, He is a sovereign being...But what would happen if the sinner said, if God wants to save me He will?  They would die and go to hell.  God has already done every thing for healing, and for salvation. Its up to men to learn what they need to do, and yes they do have a part to play. Faith is the currency of heaven. Men need to know what faith is, and what faith is not. And they need to know how to get faith, and how to use their faith.  If you don't know these things, you need to learn about them. And you should be able to explain from the bible what these things are. There is certainly a war on language these days, that the devil is waging on christian words, that men might not understand. I know there is many christian words that are becoming movie titles that are not linked to the meaning of the word, in any way what so ever. But its a detraction technique to make people think of the movie, and not what christians will tell them, when christians will be explaining some thing.
author: Shane Bob
